commit.message: Added fallback for `gnome` theme names to icongetter.
Implemented MIME-type based icon detection.
Don't check size inside `is_excutable_file()`.
Use `is_executable_file()`, when determining command path.
Introduced core-function `get_command_path()`, now used by `is_command()` (and made implementation much simpler).
`icongetter` now returns special icon for folders.
Application now has a custom window icon.
Made `launcher` to a required argument in `LaunchEdit`.
Added option to show descriptive text for the `LaunchEdit` and let the `LaunchWidget` use it.
Do not mention use of PyXDG in `Icon`-docstring.
Use label size when updating pixmap for icon.
Request path for large icon size in `Icon`, when falling back to `icongetter`.
Made `Icon.getIconPath()` "private".
Fallback to `icongetter`-functions in `Icon()` only if Qt-methods failed.
Switched back to `QItemDelegate`.
Described the purpose of `Icon`-class more detailed.
Implemented `hasThemeIcon()` for `Icon`-widget.
Updated year in copyright-line.
Use `.stringutils.convert()` for string-conversion in `Icon`-widget.
`Icon`-widget now supports `.name()`.
Made little rephrasing in `LaunchWidget`s docstring.
Options to set current icon theme on GUI widgets.
Rephrased note related to use of Qt`s naming scheme in GUI-code.
Switched to `QStyledItemDelegate`.
Rephrased docstring for the delegate`s drawDisplay() method.
Delegate now just reimplements drawDisplay() instead of paint().
Rephrased CommandIconLabel`s docstring.
gui.py now meets Qt’s naming conventions.
Introduced gui.Icon().
Made get_icon_path() easier to use.
Simplified icongetter API.
Prefixed size values in icon label with `max_`.
Added `launcher`-argument to `LaunchEdit`.
Added `completiongetter`-argument to `CommandlineCompleter`.
Mention use of `MarkedCompletionDelegate` in completer`s docstring.
Use the name `ellipsis` inside markup-creation code.
Removed unused import.
Introduced `mark_fragment`-option for completer.
Implemented delegate-property.
Refactored rendering.
Comment logger creation.
Changed logger name to format `filename(pid)`, when created by binary.
Extended `set_icon_by_command()`-docstring.
Get theme name via a property.
Pass executable's full -path to logger.
Explain expected object type for `CommandIconLabel().icon` property.
Some refactoring in `logger.py` and `logger.enable()` now takes a `name`-argument. When started as a binary, Launchit uses the binary`s file name as the logger name.
`_stringutils.convert()` is now able to handle any kind of string-type.
Removed `levelname` from logging messages.
`logging.enable()` / `logging.disable()`
Changed logger message, when config file was *found*.
Log use of config file.
Moved menu-file path request into `iter_menu_files()`.
`bin/launchit` uses `update_config()`.
Introduced `settings.update_config()`.
Use `None` instead of `CONFIG_FILENAME` as the default value for `filename` (more flexible).
CONFIG_FILENAME
Enable logging, when invoked as an executable.
Rewrote description of `bin/launchit`.
Redesigned `logger` and added `SHOULD_LOG`.
Introduced simple logging framework
Changed docstring of `gui.MarkedCompletionDelegate()` to describe its new "signal-slot-behaviour".
`gui.py`: Introduced the `fragment_updated`-signal on `CommandlineCompleter()`. This is now used by `MarkedCompletionDelegate()` in order to know, whether it should update its marking state.

`gui.py`: Widgets now specify their parent on creation. Note that the argument's name (e.g. `parent`) is explicitly mentioned where possible, to avoid confusion in cases where the class constructor of a widget accepts more arguments than just `parent`.
Modified two docstrings inside `gui.py`.
`gui.LaunchWidget()`: Removed `.update()`, since the icon is now updated by a direct call to `CommandIconLabel().set_icon_by_command()`.
Introduced `._make_layout()` in `gui.LaunchWidget()` and moved the code to create the widget's layout into it.
`icongetter.get_iconpath()`: Explicitly check resulting path for `None` after call to underlying PyXDG-function to better clarify the intention.

Introduced `.update_icon()` inside `gui.CommandIconLabel()`, which now replaces `gui.Icon()`. In addition, the `icon`-argument inside `CommandIconLabel.__init__()` has gone. The icon is now set directly via the `._icon`-attribute of the instance in order to improve readability.
Introduced `gui.ICON_THEME`, which is now used by `.set_icon_by_command()` inside `gui.CommandIconLabel()`.
Now using `.lstrip()` in `icongetter.is_iconfile()` to make more clear what is done there.
Restructured function order inside `icongetter.py`.
Wrote documentation for `gui.py`.
Introduced `gui.CompletionMarkupBuilder()` to separate markup building from the delegate.
Rewrote the `README` file, since it wasn\t up-to-date.
Introduced `core.get_trimmed()`, which is now used inside the `icongetter` module, when a command path needs to get shortened.
`icongetter.get_iconpath()` now takes more care of `icongetter.ICONFILE_EXTENSIONS`, when the icon path is retrieved from the underlying PyXDG function.
Introduced `icongetter.is_iconfile()`, which is now used by `icongetter.get_iconpath()`. Modified the latter's docstring to honour the resulting change of its behaviour.

Check existence of resulting path inside `icongetter.get_iconpath()`, since the underlying function is not doing this for absolute path names. As those names are now "officially" supported, this feature was added to the function's docstring.
Use `os.pardir` instead of `..` inside `bin/launchit`.
Refactored and commented `bin/launchit`.
Always add `package_path` to the start of the python path inside the launchit executable's `main()`-function.
Added `bin/launchit` to allow direct invocation of the GUI.
Changed text of `TypeError` inside `_stringutils.convert()` to be more general.
Updated docstring in `_stringutils.py` to make the function of this module more clear.
Added "forgotten" `@keep_string_type` to `icongetter.get_iconpath_for_commandline()`.
Introduced `_stringutils.keep_string_type`, which is now used as a decorator on various functions inside `icongetter.py`.
Added metainfo for author, license and version to `__init__.py`.
Created docstring inside `__init__.py` to explain launchit's main features.
Import `settings` inside `__init__.py`.
`gui.run_app()` now accepts the optional argument `title` and uses its value to set the window title.
Introduced `gui.Icon()`, which is now used inside `gui.CommandIconLabel()`, to ease handling of situations where no icon path could be retrieved and therefore `None` must be passed.
Introduced `icongetter.get_iconpath()`, which is now used inside `icongetter.get_iconpath_for_commandline()`.
Introduced `gui.main()`.
Changed comment in `gui.LaunchWidget()` to make more clear, why `.update()` is explicitly called at the end of initialization.

`.update()` inside `gui.LaunchWidget()` is now guaranteed to emit a `textChanged`-signal, even if the same text, which the widget already had before, was passed. Its fragment argument became optionally.
Users are now able to (optionally) define the icon theme name to use for command icons.

`update()` inside `gui.LaunchWidget()` now sets given string on its `LaunchEdit()` and changes there are connected with the `CommandIconLabel()`, so that now every part should be able to notice a (programmatically) call of that method.
Replaced "forgotten" use of `to_native_string()` with `convert()` inside `icongetter.iter_command_icons()`.
The GUI is now using `icongetter` to display suitable command icons.
Correction in `icongetter.get_iconpath_for_commandline()`: Don't convert the resulting icon path if it is `None`.
Introduced `_stringutils.convert()`, which is now used by several functions.
`icongetter.get_iconpath_for_commandline()` is now able to handle "empty" `cmdline`s.
`icongetter.guess_icon_name()` now returns the same string-type which the given `path` has (alternate/native).
Updated module docstring in `icongetter.py`, since detection isn't limited to starter icons any more.
Replaced use of `shlex.split()` with `core.parse_commandline()` inside `icongetter.iter_command_icons()`.
Introduced `icongetter.get_iconpath_for_commandline()`.
Implemented rudimentary icon name guessing.
Introduced `core.splitenv()`, which is now used by `core.get_path_dirs()`.
The program starter may now be changed via `settings.config` (default: xdg-open). The function `core.xdg_open()` was therefore renamed into `open_with_starter()`.
`icongetter.py` now reads `settings.config` to obtain the menu's directory.
Explicitly use "dot-form" for relative imports.
`_stringutils.py` now reads `settings.config` for string encoding.
Implemented `settings.config` as a skeleton, which will later hold user-defined settings.
Made corrections and additions to `settings.iter_config_entries()`s docstring.
Changed `filename` in `settings.get_config_path()` to a default keyword argument.
Extended docstring in `settings.get_user_config()`.
Introduced ``settings.py``.
`icongetter` is now imported by `__init__.py`.
Corrected a mistake in `icongetter.iter_menu_files()`: Its docstring referred to MENU_PATH, but the constant is named MENU_DIR.
Introduced the `icongetter`-module to detect the icon name for a command using PyXDG.
Deleted sharps after "High-level functions".
Introduced the `_stringutils` module, which is now used to handle string type checks and conversions.
Made `core.is_command()` able to also handle absolute path names.
Removed `XDGOpenError` exception.
Replaced the `xdg_open()` arguments `stdout` and `stderr` with the `silent`-flag and changed `launch()` to use that new version.
`core.launch()` now runs executables via `subprocess.Popen()` instead of `subprocess.call()`.
Added special handling for oversized completion names, which do not fit into the popup.
Added a shebang to `gui.py`.
`gui.py` does not any more require to be imported within the launchit path.
`core.get_name_completions()` should now handle any case of byte/unicode input correctly.
Made some changes to better reflect the meaning of `core.xdg_open()`s arguments.
`core.parse_commandline()` now acts consistent, when dealing with str or bytes/unicode.
Introduced `_altstring` and `_to_alternate_string()` in `core.py`.
Introduced gui.MarkedCompletionDelegate(), which is now used to render marked fragments on a completion.
Introduced core.get_marked_completion().
Renamed CmdlineCompleter() inside gui.py into CommandlineCompleter().
Documented and commented core.parse_commandline().
core.LaunchError() now raises error message based on interpreted arguments instead of the original cmdline.
Renamed "private" function _tostring() inside core.py into _to_native_string()
Restructured the order of functions, exceptions and constants inside core.py.
Removed str()-cast from gui.LaunchEdit.launch(), since it has become unneeded.
core.parse_commandline() now handles unicode.
core.launch() now does its parsing inside core.parse_commandline().
Changed README to state that PySide is used.
Switched from PyQt to PySide.
Changed CmdlineCompleter.update() to take `fragment` as a positional argument instead of a keyword argument
Python files now live in the "launchit" sub-folder
"Polished" a sentence in README
Wrote some description in README file
Created license text file
initial commit, implemented basic functionality

commit_comments.body: `icon-theme`-part should have been splitted into an own commit. Sorry...
